{"TopicId":206291,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How to turn on periapsis and apoapsis?","CreatedByName":"enio","CreatedById":218466,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T09:23:21Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"enio","CreatedById":218466,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T09:23:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhawk","CreatedById":131400,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T15:03:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/218466-enio/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022218466\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/218466-enio/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@enio\u003C/a\u003E and welcome to the KSP Forum!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are playing in career mode, you must upgrade the tracking station before you can see the apoapsis and periapsis markers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nHappy landings!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T15:30:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073609\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641481427\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131400\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starhawk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, Starhawk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/218466-enio/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022218466\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/218466-enio/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@enio\u003C/a\u003E and welcome to the KSP Forum!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are playing in career mode, you must upgrade the tracking station before you can see the apoapsis and periapsis markers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nHappy landings!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s not entirely accurate.\u00A0 You can see the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E markers on the map screen regardless of building upgrades, and you can even right-click on them and see their values.\u00A0 Additionally, you can click on the little purple button (maneuvers) in the lower left corner of the screen and see the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E values.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat you cannot do without upgrading Mission Control and the Tracking Station (both to level 2) is create maneuver nodes or see time to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E (same purple button in the lower left corner).\u00A0 But, we will need \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/218466-enio/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022218466\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/218466-enio/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@enio\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0to be a little more specific as to what his actual question is (with screenshots, if possible) to know what is going on here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T19:26:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073616\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641483020\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s not entirely accurate.\u00A0 You can see the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E markers on the map screen regardless of building upgrades, and you can even right-click on them and see their values.\u00A0 Additionally, you can click on the little purple button (maneuvers) in the lower left corner of the screen and see the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E values.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat you cannot do without upgrading Mission Control and the Tracking Station (both to level 2) is create maneuver nodes or see time to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E (same purple button in the lower left corner).\u00A0 But, we will need \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/218466-enio/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022218466\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/218466-enio/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@enio\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0to be a little more specific as to what his actual question is (with screenshots, if possible) to know what is going on here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnono, I am doing a caveman right now, I would know if the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E values were visible. And they would make my life a lot simpler.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, for the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, the answer is the same: must upgrade tracking station\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T19:41:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073783\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641497205\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022king of nowhere\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, king of nowhere said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnono, I am doing a caveman right now, I would know if the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E values were visible. And they would make my life a lot simpler.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, for the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, the answer is the same: must upgrade tracking station\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo am I.\u00A0 Check the following screen shot:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kRsJNw4.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.21\u0022 height=\u0022548\u0022 width=\u0022975\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/kRsJNw4.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the lower left hand corner, if you click the purple button you get \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E information.\u00A0 You don\u0027t get time to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E, but you still get in-flight \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E values.\u00A0 Also, if you look in the center of the image, you can right-click on the markers in the map view and get the values.\u00A0 This is an unmodded (I have TWP, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E, and Atmospheric Effects installed, none of which alter gameplay or physics) version of KSP, and this is stock functionality.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T20:08:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073789\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641498087\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo am I.\u00A0 Check the following screen shot:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/kRsJNw4.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kRsJNw4.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.21\u0022 height=\u0022548\u0022 width=\u0022975\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/kRsJNw4.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the lower left hand corner, if you click the purple button you get \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E information.\u00A0 You don\u0027t get time to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, but you still get in-flight \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E values.\u00A0 Also, if you look in the center of the image, you can right-click on the markers in the map view and get the values.\u00A0 This is an unmodded (I have TWP, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, and Atmospheric Effects installed, none of which alter gameplay or physics) version of KSP, and this is stock functionality.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mU3bM2i.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://imgur.com/mU3bM2i.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell, it doesn\u0027t do it for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni get the numbers, yes, of course. but it doesn\u0027t show markers on the map.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know why our games work different\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T20:38:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073802\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641499693\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022king of nowhere\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, king of nowhere said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/mU3bM2i.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mU3bM2i.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://imgur.com/mU3bM2i.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell, it doesn\u0027t do it for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni get the numbers, yes, of course. but it doesn\u0027t show markers on the map.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know why our games work different\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if it isn\u0027t doing it because it\u0027s a probe?\u00A0 Can you check to see if you can see it using a piloted command module?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T20:50:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073814\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641501487\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if it isn\u0027t doing it because it\u0027s a probe?\u00A0 Can you check to see if you can see it using a piloted command module?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit doesn\u0027t either\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T20:54:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073821\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641502207\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022king of nowhere\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, king of nowhere said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit doesn\u0027t either\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHuh.\u00A0 I know I\u0027m running an older version (1.8.1), so I wonder if this is the reason?\u00A0 Again, I don\u0027t have any mods that would do this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-10T01:35:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073821\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641502207\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022king of nowhere\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/6/2022 at 12:50 PM, king of nowhere said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit doesn\u0027t either\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHad a thought on this.\u00A0 I wonder if this is due to you trying nano-crystalline, and thus you have some really difficult settings?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-10T07:37:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073823\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641502481\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/6/2022 at 9:54 PM, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHuh.\u00A0 I know I\u0027m running an older version (1.8.1), so I wonder if this is the reason?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVarious \u0022I can\u0027t see my apoapsis\u0022 posts started cropping up after 1.12, so it\u0027s either an intended change in that version, or a bug.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OHara","CreatedById":162784,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-10T19:30:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a suspicious, and very difficult-to-parse,\u00A0 entry in the changelog:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E* Fix Ap and Pe markers appearing in future patches \n    in space not aligned to current patch\n  rendering when in career games\n  that have yet to have patched conics available.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI remember that I depended on switching to map view to see the apoapsis, in order to learn how to get into orbit in KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust to let the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E know, many players here recommend that new players start in \u0022\u003Cs\u003ESandbox\u003C/s\u003E\u0022 \u0022\u003Cu\u003EScience\u003C/u\u003E\u0022 mode.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Career\u0022 mode makes the early game difficult -- and difficult in a not-fun way, when you are still learning the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-01-15T17:41:48Z\u0022 title=\u002201/15/2022 05:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 15, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by OHara\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eoh yeah, \u0026#039;Science\u0026#039; mode reveals the parts gradually, but enables gameplay aids like Ap/Pe and pilot SAS\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mahnarch","CreatedById":114432,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-13T19:58:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224075635\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641843016\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OHara\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/10/2022 at 2:30 PM, OHara said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E~many players here recommend that new players start in \u0022Sandbox\u0022 mode.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Career\u0022 mode makes the early game difficult -- and difficult in a not-fun way, when you are still learning the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve experienced the opposite.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I started back in the day I tried sandbox but, was inundated with huge-mclarge-big parts that I shouldn\u0027t have had any business playing with, yet - until I learned basic rocketry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStarting with scraps found on the side of the road actually worked better for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-14T10:11:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgreed. Don\u0027t start in sandbox or in career... start in \u003Cem\u003Escience mode\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame limited parts pool as career, but without money or reputation or contracts being involved. All you gotta do is collect science to unlock new parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}